<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Second defense of the year. The Greater Chennai Corporation planning panel is your peers.</p>
  <p>Unit 2's defense day. Readings are submitted in the first 10 minutes; the next 45 is the share-out itself — 3 min + 2 min Q&amp;A per student, with the class playing the Greater Chennai Corporation planning panel. The first time you used this audience role was a long-form written piece; today is the oral version. Most of you used the <a href="/ai-partners/defense-practice-partner/">Defense Practice Partner</a> last night — that's the right move.</p>
  <p>The unit-close reflection asks one question: what's the most important thing about <em>landscape as a way of seeing</em> you know now that you didn't three weeks ago? The point isn't the content (you know weathering, erosion, etc. — that's the K/U). The point is whether you've internalized the move: <em>landscape is a record of processes happening at different timescales</em>. If yes, U3 builds on it directly.</p>
</section>

